Use the standard library
This is how to factorize of n:
  Remember that factors is []
  Remember that divisor is 2
  Remember that remaining is n
  Do this n times:
    When remainder of remaining and divisor is 0, then:
      Add factors to divisor
      Remember that remaining is quotient of remaining and divisor
      When remaining is 1, then:
        Leave the loop
      End when
    But, if not:
      Increase divisor by 1
    End when
  End do
  The answer is factors
Now you know